    "He worked for the esteemed historian of Renaissance art, <a href=\"/berensonb\">Bernard Berenson</a>, at the Villa I Tatti in Florence before returning to the United States.": [],
    "There he became art critic for the <em>Studio International</em> in 1927 in New York.": [],
    "In 1929 he became editor of the <em>Antiquarian</em> and later <em>Fine Arts</em> magazine (through 1934).": [
        [
            3,
            7,
            [
                "1929,"
            ]
        ]
